1
00:00:01,301 --> 00:00:03,002
-Jack, we talked --
I've seen you in concert.

2
00:00:03,002 --> 00:00:04,203
-Yeah.
-I've seen you perform.

3
00:00:04,203 --> 00:00:06,339
Please go see
Tenacious D in concert.

4
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:08,474
-Thank you.
-It's unbelievable.

5
00:00:08,474 --> 00:00:10,143
And you do a -- you do a thing

6
00:00:10,143 --> 00:00:11,844
with a thing called
the Sax-A-Boom.

7
00:00:11,844 --> 00:00:13,479
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.
-It's a toy, or -- What was it?

8
00:00:13,479 --> 00:00:15,915
-Well, it's like a saxophone,
but it's a Sax-A-Boom.

9
00:00:15,915 --> 00:00:17,716
It's a -- It's a different
kind of instrument.

10
00:00:17,716 --> 00:00:20,653
A lot of people confuse them.
-People confuse them?

11
00:00:20,653 --> 00:00:22,621
-Well, you know,
'cause they look similar.

12
00:00:22,621 --> 00:00:24,758
But a Sax-A-Boom is
its own kind of instrument

13
00:00:24,758 --> 00:00:26,225
that takes years to master.

14
00:00:26,225 --> 00:00:27,693
But, yeah,
thank you for remembering

15
00:00:27,693 --> 00:00:29,762
about my Sax-A-Boom days.

16
00:00:29,762 --> 00:00:33,399
-Well, I was just wondering,
if we happen to have one here...

17
00:00:33,399 --> 00:00:35,201
-What?
-...could you maybe just show us

18
00:00:35,201 --> 00:00:37,203
what it's like to --
-You don't have a Sax--

19
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:39,105
Oh, my God!

20
00:00:39,105 --> 00:00:41,441
[ Cheers and applause ]

21
00:00:41,441 --> 00:00:44,109
-This is a Sax-A-Boom.
-Are you kidding me?

22
00:00:44,109 --> 00:00:45,378
-This is a real -- This is a --

23
00:00:45,378 --> 00:00:48,214
You know how hard it was
to find a Sax-A-Boom?

24
00:00:48,214 --> 00:00:50,616
Could you show us
the -- the magic?

25
00:00:50,616 --> 00:00:52,385
Could you give us
a little taste?

26
00:00:52,385 --> 00:00:53,820
-Here it is.
Rare as a Stradivarius.

27
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:55,588
Yes, I will give you a taste.

28
00:00:55,588 --> 00:00:58,725
[ Laughter ]

29
00:00:58,725 --> 00:01:01,294
Are you ready?
-Yeah. Wow.

30
00:01:02,996 --> 00:01:06,032
[ Laughter ]

31
00:01:06,032 --> 00:01:09,234
[ Sax-A-Boom plays ]

32
00:01:09,234 --> 00:01:11,204
One, two, three, four.

33
00:01:11,204 --> 00:01:13,539
One, two, three, mother [bleep].

34
00:01:13,539 --> 00:01:15,674
[ Sax-A-Boom plays ]

35
00:01:15,674 --> 00:01:17,710
One, two, three, four!

36
00:01:17,710 --> 00:01:20,046
[ Sax-A-Boom plays ]

37
00:01:20,046 --> 00:01:28,621
♪♪

38
00:01:28,621 --> 00:01:36,095
♪♪

39
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:38,030
[ The Roots join ]

40
00:01:38,030 --> 00:01:41,968
♪♪

41
00:01:41,968 --> 00:01:45,905
♪♪

42
00:01:45,905 --> 00:01:49,842
♪♪

43
00:01:49,842 --> 00:01:54,346
♪♪

44
00:01:54,346 --> 00:01:56,716
-That is how you do it
right there, everybody!

45
00:01:56,716 --> 00:01:58,318
That is Jack Black!

46
00:01:58,318 --> 00:02:02,622
Go see "The House with a Clock
in Its Walls," opening tomorrow.

47
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:05,191
More with Jack Black when
we come back, everybody.

48
00:02:05,191 --> 00:02:11,231
